# Project Guidelines

## Code Style

- All documentation, comments, and docstrings must be in English
- Use `uv run` for all commands (never bare `python` or `pip`)
- Use Conventional Commits for commit messages (`feat:`, `fix:`, `docs:`, etc.)

## Tests

- Use `@pytest.mark.parametrize` instead of duplicating similar test methods
- Group related tests in test classes (`class TestXxx:`)

## Project Structure

- Single package: `munio` (flat layout at `src/munio/`)
- Single pyproject.toml at root
- Single CLI entry point: `munio` (`munio scan`, `munio check`, `munio gate`, `munio serve`, `munio policy`, `munio audit`, `munio init`, `munio status`, `munio restore`, `munio stats`, `munio version`)
- Public API: `from munio import Guard, Scanner, Verifier`
- Error classes: MunioError, MunioScanError
- Tests: `tests/core/`, `tests/scan/`, `tests/gate/`
- Constraints: `constraints/` at repo root

## Security Rules

When writing or modifying code in this project, follow these rules.

### Error handling
- NEVER use `str(exc)` in HTTP responses or data returned to callers. Log the exception, return a generic message.
- NEVER return `[]` from an `except` block in solver/verifier/adapter code — this is fail-open.
- All adapters and server endpoints must be fail-closed: `except Exception` → block (not skip).

### Type safety
- ALWAYS check `isinstance(x, bool)` BEFORE `isinstance(x, int)`.
- NEVER use `str(None)` or `str(list)`.

### Z3 / solver
- When a COMPOSITE expression contains `/`, ALL Z3 variables MUST be `z3.Real()`.
- ALL divisor variables MUST have `z3.Not(var == 0)` constraints.

### String handling
- ALL user-provided string values MUST pass through `_sanitize_string()` before matching.
- ALWAYS `casefold()` BOTH sides before `fnmatch.fnmatchcase()`.
- ONLY use `yaml.safe_load()` — NEVER `yaml.load()`.

### HTTP / API
- CORS default MUST be empty list `[]` — NEVER `"*"`.
- HTTP request models use `extra="ignore"`, NOT `extra="forbid"`.
- Health/info endpoints MUST NOT expose constraint details.
